    <item>
      <title>Semiotic Universe Lean Formalization</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/library/relationality/domains/universes/semiotic-universe/domains/formalization/domains/lean/readme/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 07 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/library/relationality/domains/universes/semiotic-universe/domains/formalization/domains/lean/readme/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;lean-formalization-of-the-semiotic-universe&#34;&gt;Lean Formalization of the Semiotic Universe&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Lean 4 + Mathlib formalization of the&#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;../../semiotic-universe.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;semiotic universe&lt;/a&gt; specification.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;approach&#34;&gt;Approach&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This formalization takes the &lt;strong&gt;axiomatic&lt;/strong&gt; approach: it postulates&#xA;that H is a Heyting algebra and that j and G satisfy certain&#xA;properties, then proves that the derived lemmas follow. The axioms&#xA;are justified by the constructive arguments in the spec (H = Sub(Y)&#xA;in a topos, j is a Lawvere-Tierney topology, etc.), but the&#xA;construction itself is not formalized here.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
